Proposed (29.8s): Use this when the user returns to an agent-driven project after stepping away and wants to get back up to speed — a fast, plain-English account of what you and other agents did while they were gone, why it was done, and what decisions now need their input. This is the classic "I've been heads-down elsewhere, catch me up / where are we / what changed / what did you get done" situation: they want the shape of recent progress and the open choices, not a diff or file-by-file log. Trigger for any return-and-orient intent however it's worded — being afk or out, back from lunch, checking in after days away, or asking what to point you at next. Don't trigger for explaining external tech or general concepts, fetching one file's diff or a single deploy's status, recapping pasted text, or writing a changelog file.

